\f0\b\fs48 \cf0 \strokec2 AGREEMENT 1 OF 4\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa298\partightenfactor0

\fs36 \cf0 ProLnk Charter Partner Agreement\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa280\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf0 Level 1 \'97 Charter Partner\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs24 \cf0 This Charter Partner Agreement ("Agreement") is entered into as of the date of electronic acceptance ("Effective Date") by and between ProLnk, LLC, a Texas limited liability company ("Company"), and the individual or entity identified during the enrollment process ("Charter Partner").\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \strokec0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa280\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf0 \strokec2 1. RECITALS\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs24 \cf0 The Company operates a technology platform connecting licensed home service professionals with homeowners through AI-assisted property documentation, lead routing, and job management tools (the "Platform"). The Charter Partner desires to participate in the Company's network growth program under the terms set forth herein.\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \strokec0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa280\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf0 \strokec2 2. CHARTER PARTNER STATUS\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs24 \cf0 Charter Partner status is a limited designation granted exclusively to the first twenty-five (25) individuals accepted into the Company's founding network. This status is non-transferable and may not be sold, assigned, gifted, or otherwise conveyed to any third party without the prior written consent of the Company.\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \strokec0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa280\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf0 \strokec2 3. OBLIGATIONS OF THE CHARTER PARTNER\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs24 \cf0 3.1 Active Subscription. The Charter Partner shall maintain an active ProLnk platform subscription at the then-current standard rate ($149.00 per month as of the Effective Date, subject to change with thirty (30) days' written notice).\
3.2 Minimum Activity Requirement. To remain eligible for network income described in Section 4, the Charter Partner must complete a minimum of two (2) documented jobs per calendar month through the Platform. Failure to meet this threshold for two (2) consecutive months will result in suspension of network income payments until the requirement is met again. Payments are not forfeited retroactively; only future payments are suspended during inactive periods.\
3.3 Network Development. The Charter Partner is encouraged, but not required, to introduce other licensed home service professionals to the Platform. The Charter Partner shall not make any representations about income potential to prospective members that are inconsistent with the disclosures provided by the Company.\
3.4 Compliance. The Charter Partner shall comply with all applicable federal, state, and local laws, including but not limited to contractor licensing requirements, and shall maintain all required licenses and insurance in good standing.\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \strokec0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa280\partightenfactor0

