4.2 Payment Schedule. Network income is calculated on the last day of each calendar month and disbursed within ten (10) business days of the following month, provided the Charter Partner's account is in good standing and the minimum payout threshold of $50.00 has been reached. Amounts below the threshold roll forward to the following month.\
4.3 No Guarantee of Income. The Company makes no representation or guarantee of any specific income level. Compensation is entirely dependent on the Charter Partner's activity and the activity of their downline network.\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \strokec0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa280\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf0 \strokec2 5. TERM AND TERMINATION\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs24 \cf0 5.1 Term. This Agreement shall commence on the Effective Date and continue indefinitely unless terminated as provided herein.\
5.2 Termination by Charter Partner. The Charter Partner may terminate this Agreement at any time by canceling their Platform subscription. Upon termination, all network income rights cease immediately.\
5.3 Termination by Company. The Company may terminate this Agreement immediately upon written notice if the Charter Partner: (a) violates any material term of this Agreement; (b) engages in fraudulent activity on the Platform; (c) loses required professional licensure; or (d) makes materially false representations to prospective network members.\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \strokec0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa280\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf0 \strokec2 6. COMPANY SALE, MERGER, OR ACQUISITION \'97 CONTINUITY OF NETWORK INCOME\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs24 \cf0 6.1 Acknowledgment of Business Risk. The Charter Partner acknowledges and understands that the Company may, at any time and in the Company's sole discretion, be sold, merged, acquired, transferred, or otherwise undergo a change of control or ownership (collectively, a "Business Transfer").\
6.2 No Guaranteed Continuity Upon Business Transfer. In the event of a Business Transfer, the continuation, modification, or termination of the network income rights described in Section 4 of this Agreement shall be determined solely by the acquiring party, successor entity, or new owner (collectively, the "Successor"). The Company makes no representation, warranty, or guarantee that any Successor will assume, honor, or continue the compensation obligations set forth herein.\
6.3 Release of Company Liability. The Charter Partner expressly agrees that the Company, its officers, directors, members, employees, and agents shall bear no liability whatsoever for any modification, reduction, suspension, or termination of network income rights that occurs as a result of a Business Transfer. The Charter Partner's sole recourse, if any, shall be against the Successor, and only to the extent the Successor has expressly assumed such obligations in writing.\
6.4 Good Faith Effort. The Company agrees to make reasonable, good faith efforts to negotiate the continuation of Charter Partner network income rights as part of any Business Transfer transaction; however, the outcome of such negotiations is not guaranteed and shall not create any enforceable obligation on the part of the Company or any Successor.\
6.5 Notice. In the event of a Business Transfer that materially affects network income rights, the Company shall provide Charter Partners with no less than thirty (30) days' written notice prior to the effective date of such change, to the extent practicable and permitted by the terms of the Business Transfer.\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \strokec0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa280\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf0 \strokec2 7. INTELLECTUAL PROPERTY AND CONFIDENTIALITY\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs24 \cf0 The Charter Partner shall not disclose any proprietary information regarding the Platform's commission structure, technology, or business model to any third party except as necessary to recruit other service professionals to the Platform in accordance with this Agreement.\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \strokec0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa280\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf0 \strokec2 8. INDEPENDENT CONTRACTOR STATUS\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs24 \cf0 The Charter Partner is an independent contractor and not an employee, agent, partner, or joint venturer of the Company. The Charter Partner is solely responsible for all taxes, insurance, and regulatory compliance related to their business activities.\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \strokec0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa280\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf0 \strokec2 9. LIMITATION OF LIABILITY\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs24 \cf0 In no event shall the Company's aggregate liability to the Charter Partner under this Agreement exceed the total network income paid to the Charter Partner in the three (3) months immediately preceding the event giving rise to the claim.\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \strokec0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa280\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf0 \strokec2 10. GOVERNING LAW AND DISPUTE RESOLUTION\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs24 \cf0 This Agreement shall be governed by the laws of the State of Texas. Any dispute arising under this Agreement shall be resolved by binding arbitration in Dallas County, Texas, under the rules of the American Arbitration Association.\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \strokec0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa280\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf0 \strokec2 11. ENTIRE AGREEMENT\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs24 \cf0 This Agreement constitutes the entire agreement between the parties with respect to its subject matter and supersedes all prior agreements, representations, and understandings.\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
